OL,7,FRobert O'Sullivan KC, prosecuting,
OL,8,Fsaid there was a "significant degree
OL,9,Fof planning" and said: "The defendant
OL,10,Farmed himself with a large kitchen
OL,11,Fknife from his home address and he
OL,12,Ftook it with him to the cemetery that
OL,13,Fmorning while he laid in wait to
OL,14,Fattack Ann Blackwood, rightly
OL,15,Fanticipating she would visit her son's
OL,16,Fgrave that day."
OL,18,FHe said that Suter attacked Ms
OL,19,FBlackwood after she arrived by bicycle
OL,20,Fand approached the grave of their son.
